 a) Keyword Detection
Checks for suspicious words like:
login, verify, secure, update, free, bonus
Logic:
If any keyword is found → mark as suspicious
Reason:
Phishing URLs often use urgency or reward-based words
 b) Number Detection
Checks if the URL contains digits
Reason:
Fraudulent domains often include random numbers to mimic legit sites
 c) Length Check
Flags URLs longer than 40 characters
Reason:
Attackers use long URLs to hide malicious parts
 d) HTTPS Verification
Checks if URL starts with https://
Reason:
Secure websites use HTTPS encryption
3. Decision Engine
A boolean flag suspicious is used
If any rule fails:
→ URL is marked fraudulent
Otherwise:
→ URL is marked safe
4. Output Generation
Displays warnings for each triggered rule
Final result:
 Fraud Link → Access Blocked
 Safe Link → Access Granted
